**[1848, 03-21] Ms.A.9.2.24.9**

Smeal, William, to MWC; Glasgow. The writer sympathizes “with the
battle-cry of {u}Abolish Slavery or Dissolve the Union.{/u}” Smeal
editor of the {u}British Friend{/u}.

“The aspect of affairs in your country is cheering both in regard to men
of political character & an increased awakening in the Churches – but my
sympathies go most with the battle-cry of {u}Abolish Slavery, or
Dissolve the Union{/u}; & I trust the veterans of the conflict in Old
Massachusetts, will not fail ever to Keep up this shout so terrific to
the slavholders.”


